Date: 1992-09-08

Title: Gauge Invariance in Chern-Simons Systems

Authors: D. Bazeia

Comments: 10 pages, Plain Tex, DF/UFPB-14/92

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D47 (1993) 734-737

We show explicitly that the question of gauge invariance of the effectivepotential in standard scalar electrodynamics remains unchanged despite theintroduction of the Chern-Simons term. The result does not depend on thepresence of the Maxwell term in the Chern-Simons territory.